00:40:12.598 --> 00:40:16.158
You just shift the IC50 anywhere between five and tenfold,

679
00:40:18.058 --> 00:40:21.278
sometimes even less than that, when you develop these mutations.

680
00:40:21.338 --> 00:40:25.238
So Wallace Bourgeois in the lab wanted to ask the question as to whether or not

681
00:40:25.278 --> 00:40:29.128
if you increase the dose in mice in a PDX experiment, how

682
00:40:29.138 --> 00:40:32.238
would that affect the development of these mutations?

683
00:40:32.278 --> 00:40:35.738
So this is a very large, as you can see, PDX experiment.

684
00:40:35.778 --> 00:40:39.458
Each one of these lines is a mouse measuring the amount of human

685
00:40:39.498 --> 00:40:41.598
leukemia cells in the peripheral blood of the mice.

686
00:40:41.938 --> 00:40:45.358
And the mice were treated with chow that had three different concentrations of

687
00:40:45.378 --> 00:40:48.478
revumenib, 0.03%, 0.1%, and

688
00:40:49.318 --> 00:40:53.278
0.3%. And we know that the 0.1% is the dose that gives us

689
00:40:53.318 --> 00:40:57.218
a very similar exposure in mice to what people are

690
00:40:57.258 --> 00:40:59.278
getting in the early-phase trials.

691
00:40:59.988 --> 00:41:03.758
And you can see those in purple. Essentially every one of these mice had a

692
00:41:03.798 --> 00:41:07.518
response, went into what you might call something like a remission in a mouse, and

693
00:41:07.558 --> 00:41:11.018
then ultimately developed very aggressive resistance.

694
00:41:11.338 --> 00:41:14.738
And in 17 of the 20 cases, those leukemias had the

695
00:41:14.798 --> 00:41:16.918
mutations that we had seen in patients.

696
00:41:17.018 --> 00:41:20.758
Interestingly enough, if you go up by threefold on the dose, one, you

697
00:41:20.938 --> 00:41:24.878
really extend the survival of the mice, and now the mutational form of

698
00:41:24.898 --> 00:41:28.378
resistance actually doesn't appear to be the most common form of resistance.

699
00:41:28.738 --> 00:41:32.638
And in fact, you get some type of low-grade persistent state, that

700
00:41:32.658 --> 00:41:36.618
the cells somehow have adapted to maintain themselves in that state.

701
00:41:36.678 --> 00:41:39.178
I'm not going to talk much more about that. That's much harder to study.

702
00:41:39.258 --> 00:41:42.318
We are studying it, but still don't quite understand what's going on there.

703
00:41:42.898 --> 00:41:46.678
But in three of the mice here that looked like they had the kinetics of

704
00:41:46.698 --> 00:41:49.838
resistance that was identical, if you will, to the

705
00:41:49.878 --> 00:41:53.458
mutational binding pocket form, had wild-type

