00:41:54.118 --> 00:41:58.058
menin. So obviously what we did then was just sequence the genomes

707
00:41:58.098 --> 00:42:01.818
or the exomes of those samples, and in fact, in two out of

708
00:42:01.878 --> 00:42:02.468
three of them,

709
00:42:03.418 --> 00:42:06.878
one of the leukemias had a 50% VAF

710
00:42:06.918 --> 00:42:07.718
heterozygous

711
00:42:08.758 --> 00:42:12.238
lysine 123 to valine mutation on MLL,

712
00:42:13.398 --> 00:42:17.298
the oncoprotein itself that obviously is binding to menin.

713
00:42:17.378 --> 00:42:21.188
And the other one, a protein called LEDGF, which is the third component of

714
00:42:21.218 --> 00:42:24.978
this complex. I didn't mention it earlier, but MLL, menin, and LEDGF

715
00:42:24.998 --> 00:42:27.958
interact with each other. I'll show you the structure of that in a minute.

716
00:42:28.458 --> 00:42:30.318
And that was one of the other mutations.

717
00:42:30.378 --> 00:42:33.578
So the leukemias are mutating the other

718
00:42:33.618 --> 00:42:37.588
proteins in the protein-protein interaction, not

719
00:42:37.618 --> 00:42:40.498
the one where the inhibitor is binding.

720
00:42:41.418 --> 00:42:45.398
We were asked by a reviewer if this happens for more

721
00:42:45.438 --> 00:42:49.258
than one of the inhibitors, so that was nice

722
00:42:49.298 --> 00:42:52.898
inasmuch as it gave us the motivation to do this experiment where we now can't put

723
00:42:52.918 --> 00:42:56.638
it in the chow. We actually have to

724
00:42:56.658 --> 00:43:00.338
